This is a neighborhood place, very friendly with food you don't mind buying. My friend lives across the street, she gets takeout here often. They have a large menu, diner style, something for everyone. They are on Grub Hub and they deliver. My friend put in the order, and it was ready and waiting for me when I arrived at the appointed time. My wife got a Munchie 'creation.' It was a sizeable roast beef sandwich, on a fresh baguette, and she asked for rare and got it. She was quite pleased with her order. She also ordered curly fries, they were crisp and tasty. I got a lunch special signature chicken kabob with secret lemon sauce. It said it came with Greek salad and pita bread. I guess the few chunks of feta, two olives, and sprinkle of oregano qualified as a Greek salad; the chicken was tender but subtle in flavor and the lemon sauce was barely noticeable even though they supplied about a watery half cup of it. It was served with rice which was cooked right but didn't have enough flavor to carry it.

Was happy with the service, kinda. I understand that it was Sunday, but it wasn't all that busy. There was 7 in our party, they accommodated us. Was very attentive. But they failed on 2 orders. I specifically requested no onions. And on the other order was chocolate chip pancakes. My order was loaded with onions, and the other order (pancakes) was just plain. The food was tasty. The home fries were over cooked. The parts that weren't over cooked tasted good.  Typical diner fare. Nothing really special.
